parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake lines can cause the brake pedal to travel to the floor, leading to a loss of braking ability, which can result in accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal travels to the floor
the vehicle fails to stop or slow down
brake fluid leaks from the brake lines
rust or corrosion on the brake lines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the hydroboost valve pump can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, making it difficult or impossible to shift gears, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.

the brake pedal does not return to its normal position

the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.
